comment: I had the opportunity to visit My Khanh tourist area and was really impressed with the cool green space, imbued with the Western river nature. Folk games such as digging ditches to catch fish or rowing canoes are not only fun but also bring interesting experiences about rural life. The cuisine here is also very rich, from garden fruits to specialties such as grilled snakehead fish or fish sauce hotpot. In particular, the tour guides are very friendly and enthusiastic, making the trip more intimate and memorable.

comment: My Khanh Tourist Village is an interesting destination in Can Tho, featuring cool green space and diverse entertainment activities. I had the opportunity to experience and was really impressed with the fresh, relaxing atmosphere here. Activities such as visiting fruit gardens, boating on the river, or participating in folk games bring a feeling very close to the cultural identity of the West.

comment: My Khanh Tourist Village, a destination not to be missed when tourists set foot in the Mekong Delta for more than twenty years. With an area of more than 30 hectares, located on the peaceful Can Tho river of the land of four-season fruit gardens "My Khanh - Phong Dien" and only a twenty-minute drive from the city center, located between two markets. Cai Rang - Phong Dien is famous for river and water trade for many generations...  My Khanh Tourist Village is a resort - entertainment - culinary - ecotourism complex with all the characteristics of the Southern river region.
